\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::1>Alicia<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>( Adopting the perspective of a woman who might get heartbroken by Evan's plan):<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I think we should consider adding another rule. The breakup is going to be extremely hard on the woman. She\u8217\'92s going to be completely unprepared if you\u8217\'92re the perfect boyfriend for one year and then abruptly end the relationship. I think your breakup day should default to the Friday following your year together. That gives her the weekend to start her recovery. However, the real rule should be flexible so you can pick the least inconvenient day to break up with her after the year has ended, even if you need to go another few weeks. If she has a big meeting, a big event, or something important coming up, you\u8217\'92ll have to wait.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs26\b1\i0\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::1>Liz<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs26\b0\i1\cf5 <$Scr_Cs::2>(Recognizing the importance of Alicia's suggested rule):<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0   \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I think flexibility on the timing of the breakup is important. Evan, you must be as considerate as possible when it comes time to end the relationship. We will make that rule #9. I think I have the final rule. I hope you fall in love with the first girl you try this with. But if you do end the relationship, I think there should be a time gap before you jump into another relationship. So, rule #10 is you must wait at least two months after the breakup to begin dating again in any capacity.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t be happier with the way this ended. He said, \u8220\'93Thank you all so much for supporting me. I realize now I did not think this through as well as I thought I had. I think these rules are great! I plan on starting this first thing tomorrow!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well, if that\u8217\'92s the case, then you all go ahead and start the poker game without me. I\u8217\'92m going to clean up this list and make copies for everyone,\u8221\'94 said Liz.}
